|YKOWhen you are killed, you become a ghost and your spirit is
whisked away to the church of the land you died in. Your corpse,
holding all of your belongings and gold, travels with you - it is
tucked safely into your inventory, so there is no corpse run and
nobody can loot you.

If you are level 5 or under, death carries no penalty at all.
Above level 5, death costs you 10% of your experience on hand.
Nothing else is lost: no stats, no levels.

At the church you have two choices:

  |YKB<pray>|YKO       Resurrect yourself. The experience loss stands.
  |YKBguild rez|YKO   Have another player resurrect you with a guild
              ability. This restores the lost experience.

Once alive, take your equipment back out of your corpse and get
back to adventuring. The emptied corpse rots away on its own.

You can also have your death avenged. A friend who avenges your
death earns a bounty of coins and experience scaled by your
killer's toughness, and your lost experience is restored. See
|YKBhelp deathavengement|YKO.

